'''Bonded Fibre Matrix''' (BFM) [[mulch]] is a unique class of [[hydroseeding]] erosion control product.

The matrix is a continuous layer of elongated fibre strands held together by a water-resistant [[Binder (material)|bonding agent]]. It keeps raindrops from hitting the soil because it has no holes larger than one millimetre. It allows no gaps between the product and the soil. It has a high [[Field capacity|water-holding capacity]]. It will not form a water-insensitive crust that can inhibit plant growth. It [[Biodegradation|biodegrades]] into materials that help plant growth.

