'''Johann Eduard Wappäus''' (17 May 1812, [[Hamburg]] &ndash; 16 December 1879, [[Göttingen]]) was a German [[geographer]]. He was a son-in-law to [[mineralogist]] [[Johann Friedrich Ludwig Hausmann]]. [[File:Göttingen-Grave.of.J.E.Wappäus.jpg|right|thumb|Gravesite of Wappäus at Cheltenhampark, Göttingen]] He studied at the Universities of [[University of Göttingen|Göttingen]] and [[University of Berlin|Berlin]], where he was a student of [[Carl Ritter]]. In 1833–34 he took part in a study trip to [[Cape Verde]] and [[Brazil]]. In 1838 he qualified as a lecturer at [[Göttingen]], where in 1845, he became an associate professor. In 1854 he was appointed professor of geography and statistics at Göttingen.<ref name=AD>[http://de.wikisource.org/wiki/ADB:Wapp%C3%A4us,_Johann_Eduard ADB: Wappäus, Johann Eduard] at [[Allgemeine Deutsche Biographie]]</ref>
His most widely known work was a new edition of the "Stein-Hörschelmann" ''Handbuchs der Geographie und Statistik'', of which, he published three exceptional volumes on the Americas.<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=X7o5AQAAMAAJ&pg=PT393&lpg=PT393&dq=%22Stein-H%C3%B6rschelmann%22+Wappaus&source=bl&ots=QGZoZPiFj0&sig=613ycvtmD-Y781isQFhElcl-BAA&hl=en&sa=X&ei=6SwWVY-ONcy4ogSe9oHYBQ&ved=0CB4Q6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=%22Stein-H%C3%B6rschelmann%22%20Wappaus&f=false The Americana: A Universal Reference Library, Volume 16] edited by Frederick Converse Beach</ref> From 1848 to 1863, and from 1874 to 1879, he was editor of the ''Göttingischen Gelehrten Anzeigen''.<ref name=AD/>
== Selected works == * ''Untersuchungen über die geographischen Entdeckungen der Portugiesen unter Heinrich dem Seefahrer : ein Beitrag zur Geschichte des Seehandels und der Geographie im Mittelalter'', 1842 &ndash; Studies on the geographical discoveries of the Portuguese under [[Henry the Navigator]]:. A contribution to the history of maritime trade and geography in the Middle Ages. * ''Deutsche Auswanderung und Colonisation'', 1846 &ndash; German emigration and colonization. * ''Handbuch der allgemeinen Geographie und Statistik'', 1855 &ndash; Textbook of general geography and statistics. * ''Allgemeine Bevölkerungsstatistik''. Leipzig : J.C. Hinrichs, (1859-1861, two volumes) &ndash; General population statistics.<ref>[http://catalog.hathitrust.org/Record/008633015 Catalog HathiTrust] Allgemeine Bevölkerungsstatistik</ref> * ''Handbuch der Geographie und Statistik von Ost- und Nord-Europa'', 1858 &ndash; Textbook of geography and statistics of eastern and northern Europe. * ''Geographie und Statistik von Mexico und Centralamerika'', 1863 &ndash; Geography and statistics of [[Mexico]] and [[Central America]]. * ''Patagonien, die Argentinische Republik, Uruguay und Paraguay geographisch und statistisch dargestellt'', 1870 &ndash; [[Patagonia]], the Republic of [[Argentina]], [[Uruguay]] and [[Paraguay]] presented geographically and statistically. * ''Handbuch der Geographie und Statistik des Kaiserreichs Brasilien'', 1871 &ndash; Textbook of geography and statistics of the [[Empire of Brazil]]. * ''Einleitung in das Studium der Statistik. Vorlesungen Gehalten an der Universität Göttingen'', 1881 &ndash; Introduction to the study of statistics. Lectures held at the University of Göttingen.<ref>[http://classify.oclc.org/classify2/ClassifyDemo?search-author-txt=%22Wapp%C3%A4us%2C+Johann+Eduard%22 OCLC Classify] list of published works.</ref>
