{{Infobox officeholder | name =Robert H. T. Smith | image = | order = | title = President of the [[University of British Columbia]] (''pro tempore'') | term=1985 | predecessor = [[George Pedersen]] | successor =[[David Strangway]] | birth_date ={{Birth date and age|1935|5|22}} | birth_place =[[Walcha, New South Wales]], [[Australia]] | death_date = | alma_mater = | spouse = | occupation=geographer }}
'''Robert Henry Tufrey Smith''' (born May 22, 1935) is an Australian-Canadian academic who was the president pro tempore of the [[University of British Columbia]] in 1985.<ref>[https://books.google.ca/books?id=lv8LAQAAMAAJ&q=%22SMITH,+Robert+Henry+Tufrey%22&dq=%22SMITH,+Robert+Henry+Tufrey%22&hl=en&sa=X&ei=2UuKVYrOIInQ-QHJvoLQCA&ved=0CCUQ6AEwAA]</ref> A professor of geography, Smith was educated at [[Australian National University]], the [[University of New England (Australia)|University of New England]] and [[Northwestern University]].<ref>[https://books.google.ca/books?id=e48dAAAAMAAJ&q=%22Smith,+Robert%22+geography+Northwestern+British+Columbia&dq=%22Smith,+Robert%22+geography+Northwestern+British+Columbia&hl=en&sa=X&ei=rkuKVYrCFcm3-QGc3KmgAg&ved=0CDkQ6AEwBw]</ref> In 1964, he was a [[Guggenheim Fellow]].<ref>[http://www.gf.org/fellows/all-fellows/robert-h-t-smith/ Fellows: Robert H. T. Smith]</ref> He is a fellow of the [[Academy of the Social Sciences in Australia]] and a member of the [[Order of Australia]].<ref>[http://www.assa.edu.au/fellowship/fellow/303 Fellows: Emeritus Professor Robert Smith AM]</ref>
